%5C%22%3Ehas%20remained%20jailed%20in%20Brooklyn%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20his%20September%2016%20arrest%20on%20federal%20sex-trafficking%20charges.%20His%20lawyers%20have%20argued%20since%20then%20that%20he%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20serve%20home%20detention%20on%20a%20%2450%20million%20bond%20while%20awaiting%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombs%20has%20also%20offered%20to%20comply%20with%20weekly%20drug%20testing%2C%20to%20have%20no%20access%20to%20phones%20or%20the%20internet%2C%20and%20to%20restrict%20those%20who%20visit%20him%20to%20family%20and%20friends%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25196850-us-v-combs-appeal-motion-information-20241008%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E31-page%20motion%20for%20pretrial%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20filed%20with%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%2C%20Second%20Circuit%2C%20in%20Manhattan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20argues%20that%20while%20judges%20gave%20a%20lengthy%20and%20detailed%20explanation%20for%20denying%20bail%20for%20Epstein%2C%20Maxwell%2C%20and%20Raniere%20%E2%80%94%20as%20required%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Farchives%2Fjm%2Fcriminal-resource-manual-26-release-and-detention-pending-judicial-proceedings-18-usc-3141-et%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20federal%20law%20section%203142(g)%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20no%20such%20detailed%20explanation%20has%20been%20made%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsean-diddy-combs-bond-court-jail-trial-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekeeping%20Combs%20confined%20pretrial.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Combs'%20lawyers%2C%20the%20district%20court%20has%20made%20a%20%26quot%3Blegal%20error%20by%20failing%20to%20make%20any%20factual%20findings%20or%20weigh%20the%20required%20factors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20US%20v%20Epstein%2C%20US%20v%20Maxwell%2C%20and%20US%20v%20Raniere%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20detention%20orders%20were%20supported%20by%20detailed%20factual%20findings%20and%20explicit%20weighing%20of%20the%203142(g)%20factors%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20appeal%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20Court%20has%20reversed%20similarly%20defective%20detention%20orders%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20appeal%20added%2C%20citing%20a%20Second%20Circuit%20reversal%20of%20a%20bail%20denial%20from%201988.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombs%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%2C%20and%20his%20lawyers%20have%20attacked%20the%20DOJ's%20case%20strenuously%20in%20prior%20court%20appearances%2C%20describing%20the%20charged%20conduct%20as%20consensual%20and%20the%20primary%20witness%20against%20him%20as%20not%20credible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday%20night's%20appellate%20filing%20reinforces%20these%20two%20themes.%20It%20describes%20the%20DOJ's%20trafficking%20case%20as%20based%20on%20sexual%20conduct%20by%20willing%20participants%20%E2%80%94%20specifically%20what%20the%20government%20described%20in%20its%20indictment%20as%20%26quot%3Bfreak%20offs%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Belaborate%20and%20produced%20sex%20performances%20that%20Combs%20arranged%2C%20directed%2C%20masturbated%20during%2C%20and%20often%20electronically%20recorded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Combs%20believes%20the%20evidence%20will%20show%20that%20to%20the%20extent%20such%20activities%20occurred%2C%20all%20individuals%20who%20participated%20were%20adults%20voluntarily%20engaged%20in%20consensual%20sex%2C%26quot%3B%20Combs%20lawyers%20wrote%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government's%20case%2C%20the%20lawyers%20argue%2C%20is%20also%20overly%20reliant%20on%20a%20single%20%26quot%3Bwidely%20publicized%20March%205%2C%202016%20video%20of%20Mr.%20Combs%20depicting%20a%20domestic%20violence%20incident%20with%20a%20former%20girlfriend.%26quot%3B%20This%20point%20in%20the%20appeal%20was%20a%20reference%20to%20footage%20showing%20Combs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsean-diddy-combs-apologizes-video-cassie-ventura-assault-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epunching%20and%20kicking%20R%26amp%3BB%20singer%20Cassie%20Ventura%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20California%20hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombs%20issued%20an%20apology%20when%20CNN%20first%20published%20the%20video%20in%20May%2C%20but%20his%20lawyers%20have%20since%20adopted%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsean-diddy-combs-attack-cassie-sex-trafficking-case-could-backfire-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20attack-the-accuser%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombs%20and%20Ventura%20shared%20%26quot%3Ba%20long-term%20loving%20relationship%20that%20became%20strained%20by%20mutual%20infidelity%20and%20jealousy%26quot%3B%20and%20which%20was%20%26quot%3Boften%20mutually%20toxic%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20lawyers%20wrote%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombs%20is%20described%20in%20the%20appeal%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%2054-y-o%20father%20of%20seven%2C%20a%20US%20citizen%2C%20an%20extraordinarily%20successful%20artist%2C%20businessman%2C%20and%20philanthropist%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20most%20recognizable%20people%20on%20earth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20appeal%2C%20signed%20by%20newly-retained%20attorney%20Alexandra%20A.%20E.%20Shapiro%2C%20additionally%20promises%20that%20Combs%20will%20not%20attempt%20to%20flee%2C%20obstruct%20justice%2C%20or%20intimidate%20witnesses%2C%20three%20major%20concerns%20cited%20by%20prosecutors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20traveled%20to%20New%20York%20to%20surrender%20because%20he%20knew%20he%20was%20going%20to%20be%20indicted.%20He%20took%20extraordinary%20steps%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20he%20intended%20to%20face%20and%20contest%20the%20charges%2C%20not%20flee%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20filing%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20steps%2C%20per%20Combs'%20lawyers%2C%20included%20relocating%20from%20Miami%20to%20a%20New%20York%20hotel%20so%20he%20could%20be%20on%20hand%20to%20surrender%2C%20putting%20his%20private%20airplane%20up%20for%