3Cp%3EI%20am%20a%20second-generation%20Chinese%20American%20and%20have%20traveled%20to%20Asia%20a%20few%20times%20to%20visit%20family%20and%20as%20a%20tourist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20eager%20to%20explore%20more%20and%20started%20looking%20at%20internships%20listed%20on%20the%20Stanford%20portal.%20There%20were%20opportunities%20to%20intern%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20or%20at%20a%20water%20park%20in%20Indonesia.%20However%2C%20the%20opportunity%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenz-farm-south-korea-free-food-lodging-gap-year-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20at%20a%20matcha%20farm%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Japan%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20a%20month%20stood%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETea%20was%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20my%20childhood.%20Growing%20up%20in%20New%20York%2C%20my%20mom%20would%20bring%20my%20sister%20and%20me%20to%20Flushing%2C%20Queens%2C%20every%20other%20weekend%20to%20enjoy%20dim%20sum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20we%20sat%20down%20at%20the%20restaurant%2C%20the%20first%20question%20the%20waiters%20asked%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20type%20of%20tea%20do%20you%20want%20to%20drink%3F%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20a%20way%20to%20reconnect%20with%20my%20Asian%20heritage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ed366309-5d68-4d02-a5aa-2cbf6d5a4077%5C%22%3EAdjusting%20to%20life%20on%20the%20farm%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20farm%2C%20D%3Amatcha%2C%20is%20located%20in%20Wazuka%2C%20an%20hour%20from%20Kyoto.%20It's%20owned%20by%20Daiki%20Tanaka%2C%20a%20Japanese%20farmer%20in%20his%20late%2030s%2C%20who%20left%20his%20job%20as%20the%20president%20of%20a%20doughnut%20company%20to%20work%20in%20agriculture.%20It's%20a%20small%20business%20with%20less%20than%2010%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20my%20first%20day%20at%20the%20farm%2C%20I%20remember%20being%20surprised%20by%20the%20sound%20of%20cicadas%20that%20filled%20the%20air.%20From%20my%20room%20on%20the%20farm%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20could%20see%20expansive%20tea%20fields.%20It%20was%20like%20nothing%20I%20had%20ever%20seen%20before.%20Room%20and%20board%20were%20covered%20during%20my%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-pay-cut-career-switch-leave-sales-job-potato-farming-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEvery%20day%20on%20the%20farm%20was%20different%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Daiki-san's%20farm%20also%20offered%20tea%20tours%20and%20had%20a%20bed%20and%20breakfast%3B%20my%20project%20was%20to%20determine%20how%20to%20improve%20the%20retention%20of%20guests%20on%20the%20farm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20my%20project%2C%20we%20created%20itineraries%20for%20guests%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eincluding%20a%20mapped-out%20walking%20trail%20in%20the%20backyard%20and%20a%20schedule%20of%20cooking%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222856%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cherie%20baking%20with%20an%20employee%20at%20the%20farm%20and%20a%20friend.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fe02e19e0c5c2eeeea3bf9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELuo%20(center)%20helped%20to%20develop%20matcha%20baking%20classes%20while%20at%20the%20farm.%3Cp%3ECherie%20Luo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20worked%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fcherie.brooke%2F%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtent%20creator%20since%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20already%20familiar%20with%20content%20marketing.%20I%20helped%20Daiki-san%20create%20videos%20to%20post%20on%20Instagram.%20I%20also%20posted%20about%20my%20time%20on%20the%20farm%20on%20my%20social%20media%20channels%2C%20which%20was%20meaningful%20as%20I%20could%20use%20my%20platform%20to%20shine%20a%20light%20on%20his%20small%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a288b4ca-5cee-42b8-b18a-30c1eca116fa%5C%22%3EIt%20opened%20my%20eyes%20to%20a%20business%20world%20outside%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findians-leaving-big-tech-to-launch-startups-back-home-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESilicon%20Valley%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20working%20at%20LinkedIn%20as%20a%20product%20manager%20for%20almost%20five%20years%20instilled%20in%20me%20the%20mindset%3A%20How%20are%20we%20growing%20our%20revenue%3F%20How%20do%20we%20grow%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20always%20been%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-and-grow-a-business-founders-advice-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehyper-growth%20mode%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that's%20how%20I%20approached%20business.%20When%20I%20presented%20Daiki-san%20with%20ideas%20on%20how%20to%20grow%20his%20business%2C%20he%20would%20explain%20how%20that%20wasn't%20what%20he%20wanted%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20would%20tell%20him%20he%20could%20scale%20and%20have%20his%20tea%20distributed%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20he%20would%20reply%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20doesn't%20sound%20fun.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaiki-san%20told%20me%20he%20was%20content%20with%20his%20company's%20speed%20of%20growth%20and%20said%20he%20prioritized%20what%20gives%20him%20energy.%20For%20him%2C%20that's%20focusing%20on%20the%20customer%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20wake-up%20call.%20As%20a%20business%20school%20student%20coming%20from%20the%20US%2C%20I%20was%20taught%20to%20optimize%20growth.%20However%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20there%20are%20different%20ways%20to%20approach%20business%20that%20do%20not%20prioritize%20growth%2C%20but%20happiness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228c1c212c-c020-4ddc-8686-e1aed1b51703%5C%22%3EI'm%20starting%20a%20matcha%20business%20with%20my%20sister%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222085%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Girl%20in%20a%20matcha%20farm%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fe03a65ccfc192a552c9d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221564%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20matcha%20farm%20was%20located%20in%20Wazuka%2C%20a%20town%20an%20hour%20from%20Kyoto.%3Cp%3ECherie%20Luo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20month%2C%20I%20had%20formed%20strong%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eworking%20relationships%20with%20Daiki-san%20and%20his%20team.%20So%20much%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdifferences-between-japanese-and-american-work-culture-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJapanese%20business%20culture%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20about%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eperson-to-person%20communication%20and%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20I%20came%20back%20to%20him.%20My%20sister%20and%20I%20had%20discussed%20leaning%20into%20our%20passions%20for%20matcha%2C%20which%20had%20been%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eon%20my%20mind%20since%20leaving%20that%20summer.%20And%20now%20we%20got%20the%20ball%20rolling%3A%20we've%20started%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsistersmatcha.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ematcha%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20business%20is%20still%20in%20its%20early%20stages%2C%20but%20we've%20opened%20pre-orders%20for%20matcha%20powder%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eon%20our%20website.%20We%20charge%20%2458%20for%2030-gram%20tins%20of%20tea%2C%20and%20the%20first%20delivery%20is%20set%20to%20take%20place%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internship%20changed%20my%20life.%20I%20wouldn't%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehave%20thought%20of%20starting%20a%20matcha%20company%20if%20I%20had%20not%20gone%20to%20Japan%20and%20spent%20time%20with%20Daiki-san.%20He%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshowed%20me%20that%20even%20though%20it's%20scary%20to%20follow%20your%20passions%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20focus%20on%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhat%20makes%20you%20happy%20and%20what%20gives%20you%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20about%20going%20ab