0nomads%20protect%20their%20livestock%20from%20snow%20leopards%2C%20thus%20preventing%20man-animal%20conflicts%2C%20he%20also%20pioneered%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20models%20of%20eco-tourism%20with%20conservation-linked%20homestays%20located%20in%20critical%20snow%20leopard%20habitats%20and%20along%20popular%20trekking%20routes.%20These%20successful%20models%20of%20community-based%20tourism%20in%20the%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20the%20Sham%20region%2C%20and%20Zanskar%20still%20stand%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20tragically%20passed%20away%20at%20the%20age%20of%20just%2042%20in%202011%20due%20to%20a%20deteriorating%20neurological%20condition%20but%20not%20before%20leaving%20behind%20a%20stellar%20legacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%3A%20The%20forest%20officer%20who%20showed%20India%20how%20to%20protect%20tigers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnown%20for%20his%20trademark%20long%20handlebar%20moustache%2C%20olive-coloured%20safari%20hat%20and%20dashing%20dark%20glasses%2C%20the%20late%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F234711%2Fhow-does-india-protect-tigers-fateh-singh-rathore-ranthambhore-national-park-rajasthan-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFateh%20Singh%20Rathore%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20the%20principal%20architect%20behind%20the%20success%20story%20that%20is%20the%20Ranthambhore%20National%20Park.%20As%20a%20ranger%2C%20warden%2C%20and%20field%20director%20at%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20best-known%20tiger%20preserves%2C%20Fateh%E2%80%99s%20work%20emphasised%20three%20things%20%E2%80%94%20natural%20regeneration%20of%20the%20habitat%2C%20constant%20engagement%20with%20local%20communities%20living%20in%20its%20vicinity%20that%20went%20way%20beyond%20consultations%2C%20and%20an%20abiding%20love%20for%20the%20creatures%20who%20inhabited%20this%20forest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20became%20the%20blueprint%20for%20what%20a%20successful%20tiger%20conservation%20strategy%20looks%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F05103523%2FFateh_Singh_Rathore_2008-500x693.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-234723%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22693%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EFateh%20Singh%20Rathore%20(Image%20courtesy%20Wikimedia%20Commons)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFateh%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20conservation%20was%20marked%20by%20his%20incredible%20knowledge%20of%20the%20terrain%20inside%20Ranthambore%E2%80%99s%20core%20area%20and%20the%20depth%20of%20his%20engagement%20with%20the%20local%20community%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%20was%20relocating%2016%20villages%20inhabited%20in%20the%20core%20area%20of%20the%20National%20Park%20and%20ensuring%20that%20the%20village%20economy%20thrived%20despite%20this%20resettlement%20and%20a%20crackdown%20on%20poaching.%20He%20nearly%20died%20for%20his%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20as%20a%20forest%20officer%2C%20his%20loyalties%20only%20lay%20with%20the%20forests%20and%20not%20politicians%20or%20superior%20officers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20feature%20of%20his%20work%20that%20would%20come%20at%20a%20great%20personal%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Jamal%20Ara%3A%20The%20first%20%E2%80%98Birdwoman%E2%80%99%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20era%20when%20the%20field%20of%20ornithology%20was%20dominated%20by%20men%2C%20Jamal%20Ara%20stood%20out%20as%20a%20pioneer.%20It%20was%20the%20legendary%20ornithologist%20Salim%20Ali%20who%20called%20her%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98Birdwoman%E2%80%99%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20present-day%20Jharkhand%2C%20her%20work%20on%20the%20ornithology%20of%20the%20Chota%20Nagpur%20plateau%20%E2%80%9Cremains%20the%20only%20comprehensive%20study%20of%20birds%20in%20the%20region%20till%20date%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20an%20essay%20by%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20titled%20%3Cem%3EThe%20First%20Lady%20of%20Indian%20Ornithology%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20published%20in%20a%20recent%20collection%20of%20essays%20titled%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FWOMEN-WILD-Brilliant-Wildlife-Biologists%2Fdp%2F9353451817%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWomen%20in%20the%20Wild%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Eedited%20by%20Anita%20Mani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20only%20studying%20till%20Class%2010%2C%20she%20was%20a%20prolific%20writer%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20birds.%20According%20to%20Kazmi%2C%20from%201949%20to%201988%2C%20she%20contributed%20to%20more%20than%2060%20papers%20and%20published%20articles%20to%20journals%20including%20the%20Bombay%20Natural%20History%20Society%20and%20Bengal%20Natural%20History%20Society%2C%20and%20the%20Newsletter%20for%20Birdwatchers%2C%20a%20publication%20read%20by%20amateur%20and%20professional%20ornithologists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20she%20also%20wrote%20a%20small%20booklet%20for%20children%20titled%20%3Cem%3EWatching%20Birds%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20by%20the%20National%20Book%20Trust%20(NBT).%20The%20book%20is%20currently%20in%20its%2013th%20edition%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20educate%20children%20on%20the%20birds%20of%20India%20in%20multiple%20languages%20till%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20her%20prolific%20writing%2C%20she%20also%20raised%20awareness%20among%20the%20masses%20through%20her%20programmes%20in%20All%20India%20Radio%20(AIR)%20and%20also%20dabbled%20in%20journalism%20for%20mainstream%20publication.%20%E2%80%9CMore%20importantly%2C%20in%20those%20days%2C%20she%20was%20the%20only%20spokesperson%20for%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20imperilled%20wilderness%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20went%20beyond%20just%20advocating%20for%20birds%2C%20according%20to%20Raza.%20Her%20prescriptions%20and%20recommendations%20would%20lay%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20groundwork%20for%20modern%20conservation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Kailash%20Sankhala%3A%20The%20unsung%20hero%20who%20changed%20the%20destiny%20of%20tigers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F223419%2Fpadma-shri-kailash-sankhala-project-tiger-kanha-sariska-india-unsung-hero-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKailash%20Sankhala%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20first%20director%20of%20Project%20Tiger%2C%20played%20a%20fundamental%20role%20in%20turning%20the%20tide%20for%20wildlife%20conservation%20in%20India%2C%20particularly%20of%20tigers.%20A%20pioneering%20field%20officer%2C%20he%20did%20real%20field%20research%20work%20to%20understand%20the%20secretive%20lives%20of%20tigers%20from%20their%20behaviour%2C%20population%20dynamics%20to%20daily%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20this%20work%20was%20triggered%20by%20an%20incident%20in%20the%20early%201950s%20when%20he%20killed%20a%20tiger.%20Riddled%20by%20guilt%2C%20it%20transformed%20him%20from%20a%20forest%20officer%20just%20issuing%20hunting%20permits%20to%20spending%20the%20remainder%20of%20his%20life%20protecting%20the%20tiger%20and%20its%20habitat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-500x628.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kailash%20Sankhala%20(Source%3A%20Amit%20Sankhala)%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-500x628.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-239x300.jpeg%20239w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-768x965.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-1223x1536.jpeg%201223w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-1631x2048.jpeg%201631w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-scaled.jpeg%202038w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-223426%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKailash%20Sankhala%20(Source%3A%20Amit%20Sankhala)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20gathering%20public%20support%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20tiger%20conservation%20in%20the%20national%20and%20international%20media%2C%20he%20first%20persuaded%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20to%20ban%20the%20export%20of%20tiger%2C%20leopard%2C%20and%20panther%20skins%20or%20the%20products%20made%20from%20them%20in%201970%20and%20ban%20the%20hunting%20of%20tigers%20altogether%20in%201972.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20later%20in%20April%201973%2C%20prime%20minister%20Gandhi%20established%20Project%20Tiger%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20and%20restore%20natural%20habitats%20of%20tigers%20and%20to%20track%20and%20protect%20the%20remaining%20wild%20tigers%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20and%20handpicked%20Sankhala%20as%20its%20first%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20S%20P%20Shahi%3A%20The%20guardian%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20wolves%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahuadanr%20Wolf%20Sanctuary%20in%20Jharkhand%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20sanctuary%20in%20India%20dedicated%20to%20wolf%20preservation%20%E2%80%94%20owes%20its%20existence%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F300043%2Fforgotten-forest-officer-sp-shahi-behind-indias-only-wolf-sanctuary-mahuadanr-jharkhand%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES%20P%20Shahi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%20and%20forest%20officer.%20Back%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20he%20paid%20close%20attention%20to%20how%20wolves%20were%20hurtling%20towards%20extinction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20noted%20how%20unlike%20most%20forest%20officers%20of%20his%20era%2C%20Shahi%20recognised%20the%20importance%20of%20what%20we%20now%20call%20%E2%80%98Open%20Natural%20Ecosystems%E2%80%99%20for%20wolves.%20These%20ecosystems%20consist%20of%20a%20range%20of%20non-forested%20habitats%20from%20savanna%20grasslands%20to%20deserts%2C%20which%20host%20a%20high%20density%20of%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20mammalian%20fauna%E2%80%9D.%20What%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20interesting%20about%20these%20ecosystems%20is%20that%20unlike%20wildlife%20sanctuaries%20and%20other%20protected%20areas%20where%20limits%20are%20set%20on%20human%20habitation%2C%20they%20support%20the%20lives%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20pastoralists%20and%20their%20livestock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22SP%20Shahi%20%26amp%3B%20the%20Indian%20grey%20wolf%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-300065%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESP%20Shahi%20%26amp%3B%20the%20Indian%20grey%20wolf%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20like%20Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%2C%20Shahi%20also%20understood%20the%20role%20of%20local%20communities%20(in%20this%20case%20pastoralists)%20in%20facilitating%20conservation.%20Beyond%20wolves%2C%20Shahi%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20Palamau%20and%20his%20meticulous%20documentation%20of%20its%20wildlife%20was%20a%20very%20key%20reason%20that%20this%20forest%20was%20declared%20as%20tiger%20reserves%20in%201973%2C%20according%20to%20P%20K%20Sen%2C%20former%20director%20of%20Project%20Tiger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20J%20Vijaya%3A%20The%20defender%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20turtles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%2018%20April%201987%2C%20the%20bodily%20remains%20of%20J%20Vijaya%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20female%20herpetologist%20and%20turtle%20field%20biologist%2C%20were%20found%20in%20Guindy%20National%20Park%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Only%2028%2C%20the%20cause%20of%20her%20death%20remains%20unknown%20to%20this%20day%20but%20what%20remains%20undeniable%20is%20the%20legacy%20she%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20off%20as%20a%20volunteer%20at%20Madras%20Snake%20Park%20in%201975%20as%20a%20college%20student%2C%20Vijaya%20(known%20to%20her%20friends%20as%20%E2%80%98Viji%E2%80%99)%20would%20go%20on%20to%20not%20only%20become%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20researchers%20of%20turtles%20but%20also%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20its%20conservation.%20To%20understand%20the%20scope%20of%20turtle%20trade%20and%20the%20exploitation%20it%20entailed%2C%20she%20would%20travel%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20this%20country%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98badlands%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Chambal%20(ravines)%20to%20the%20meat%20markets%20of%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20tribute%20penned%20by%20freelance%20journalist%20Janaki%20Lenin%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fecologise.in%2F2017%2F04%2F18%2Ftribute-viji-turtle-girl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEcologise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20black%20and%20white%20pictures%20she%20took%20of%20the%20gory%20Ridley%20sea%20turtle%20slaughter%20on%20Digha%20beach%20and%20in%20the%20meat%20markets%20of%20Calcutta%2C%20shook%20the%20public%20when%20India%20Today%20magazine%20ran%20them%20in%20the%20early%201980s.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20media%20expose%20ever%20done%20on%20the%20free-for-all%20trade%20in%20sea%20turtles%20and%20highlights%20the%20difference%20one%20individual%20can%20make%20for%20conservation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20her%20expose%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20immediately%20took%20action%20against%20the%20exploitation%20of%20sea%20turtles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Anne%20Wright%3A%20India%E2%80%99s%20adopted%20daughter%20and%20pioneer%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%204%20October%2C%202023%2C%20India%20mourned%20the%20loss%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F333222%2Fanne-wright-conservationist-wildlife-protection-act-reserves-project-tiger-legacy-raza-kazmi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%20who%20dedicated%20over%20five%20decades%20to%20protecting%20India%E2%80%99s%20wildlife.%20This%20daughter%20of%20a%20British%20civil%20servant%20decided%20to%20adopt%20India%20as%20%E2%80%98her%20country%E2%80%99%20and%20worked%20tirelessly%20to%20protect%20its%20fauna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnne%20was%20a%20true%20changemaker%2C%20breaking%20gender%20barriers%20in%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20playing%20a%20key%20role%20in%20drafting%20the%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%20of%201972%2C%20and%20driving%20the%20creation%20of%20numerous%20Protected%20Areas%2C%20including%20Palamau%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20Dalma%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary.%20She%20worked%20closely%20with%20local%20communities%20and%20bureaucracies%20to%20make%20lasting%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Late%20Anne%20Wright%20receiving%20an%20award%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333245%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELate%20Anne%20Wright%20receiving%20an%20award%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20working%20towards%20these%20critical%20causes%2C%20in%201970%2C%20she%20also%20wrote%20an%20article%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Statesman%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20describes%20in%20harrowing%20detail%20the%20illegal%20sale%20of%20tiger%20and%20leopard%20skins%20in%20Kolkata.%20The%20article%20was%20republished%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20(NYT)%2C%20causing%20a%20global%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20article%20was%20debated%20heavily%20in%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%2C%20and%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20exaggeration%20to%20say%20that%20this%20article%2C%20along%20with%20the%20damning%20photographs%20on%20the%20scale%20of%20tiger%20hunting%20especially%20for%20skin%20trade%2C%20convinced%20the%20then%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20ban%20tiger%20hunting%20the%20very%20same%20year%20(1970).%20That%20was%20the%20power%20of%20her%20pen.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Saroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%3A%20A%20parent%20to%20the%20tigress%20Khairi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%205%20October%2C%201974%2C%20a%20female%20tiger%20cub%20was%20brought%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F233080%2Ftigress-khairi-simlipal-odisha-ifs-officer-saroj-raj-choudhury-documentary-pugmark-method-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESaroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founder%20Field%20Director%20of%20the%20Similipal%20Tiger%20Reserve%20in%20the%20Mayurbhanj%20district%20of%20Odisha.%20Found%20unattended%20by%20people%20of%20the%20Kharia%20tribal%20community%2C%20Saroj%20would%20name%20her%20%E2%80%98Khairi%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20next%20seven%20years%2C%20Khairi%20would%20become%20a%20%E2%80%98free-living%20family%20member%E2%80%99%20at%20Choudhury%E2%80%99s%20official%20bungalow%20in%20Jashipur.%20She%20was%20fed%20with%20mutton%20and%20milk%20powder%2C%20slept%20on%20their%20beds%20and%20often%20played%20with%20them.%20Saroj%20closely%20observed%20her%20to%20study%20the%20various%20behavioural%20aspects%20of%20tigers%2C%20especially%20the%20use%20of%20pheromones%2C%20their%20mating%20behaviour%20and%20territoriality%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20long%20before%20Saroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%20took%20over%20as%20the%20Simlipal%20Tiger%20Reserve%E2%80%99s%20first%20Field%20Director%20and%20met%20Khairi%2C%20he%20had%20already%20established%20himself%20as%20a%20pioneer%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20particularly%20of%20tigers%2C%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20developing%20the%20pugmark%20tracking%20technique%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20the%20bedrock%20of%20organising%20tiger%20censuses%20in%20India%20till%202004%20and%20the%20foundation%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20much%20vaunted%20Project%20Tiger%20initiative%20%E2%80%94%20to%20mentoring%20generations%20of%20forest%20officers%20in%20the%20finer%20nuances%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20Choudhury%20remains%20a%20legendary%20conservationist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F17145020%2FSaroj-Raj-Choudury-12.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22684%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Saroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%20with%20Khairi%20%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-233089%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22528%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESaroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%20with%20Khairi%20(Image%20courtesy%20Twitter%2FRamesh%20Pandey%20IFS)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20Images%20courtesy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFateh_Singh_Rathore%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWikimedia%20Commons%2FFateh%20Singh%20Rathore%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FSanctuaryAsia%2Fstatus%2F956436281835360256%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%2FSanctuary%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Amit%20Sankhala%2C%20SLC-IT%2C%20Raza%20Kazmi%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Frameshpandeyifs%2Fstatus%2F1282671780729982977%3Fs%3D19%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%2FRamesh%20Pandey%20IFS%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728031345000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F05103523%2FFateh_Singh_Rathore_2008-500x693.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D368687%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20snow%20leopard%20conservationist%20Rinchen%20Wangchuk%20to%20tiger%20protection%20pioneer%20Kailash%20Sankhala%2C%20these%20individuals%20fought%20to%20protect%20endangered%20species%2C%20inspire%20community-based%20conservation%2C%20and%20challenge%20systemic%20threats.%20Their%20legacies%20continue%20shaping%20India's%20conservation%20efforts%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Rinchen%20Norbu%20Wangchuk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A76%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F368687%2Fworld-animal-welfare-day-remembering-pioneers-wildlife-conservation-india-project-tiger%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20a%20Family%20Brought%20The%20300-YO%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20Back%20to%20Life%20As%20a%20Heritage%20Site%20%26amp%3B%20Hotel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20palace%20was%20overgrown%20with%20brambles%3B%20the%20manor%20barely%20visible%20through%20the%20forests%20that%20threatened%20to%20suffocate%20it.%20Even%20the%20highest%20points%20of%20the%20castle%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20been%20spared.%20Wild%20plants%20held%20the%20towers%20in%20a%20vice-like%20grip.%20In%20some%20places%2C%20the%20roof%20had%20crumbled%3B%20in%20others%20it%20had%20shattered%2C%20closing%20off%20entrances%20and%20exits.%20No%20one%20knew%20for%20sure%20what%20the%20house%20held%20within%20it.%20Were%20there%20wild%20beasts%20lurking%20inside%3F%20Or%20something%20more%20ferocious%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%20it%20sounds%20like%20an%20excerpt%20from%20one%20of%20Grimm%E2%80%99s%20Fairy%20Tales%2C%20the%20incident%20is%20a%20real-life%20scene%20that%20awaited%20Pallab%20Roy%20(60)%20and%20his%20family%20when%20they%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F310006%2Froyal-sisters-duo-akshita-mrinalika-the-belgadia-palace-boutique-hotel-odisha-sustainable-travel%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevisited%20their%20ancestral%20palace%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Kasim%20Bazar%2C%20Murshidabad%2C%20West%20Bengal.%20The%20300-year-old%20architecture%20had%20fallen%20into%20a%20state%20of%20despair%20since%20its%20last%20occupant%2C%20Pallab%E2%80%99s%20grandfather%20Raja%20Kamalaranjan%20Roy%2C%20passed%20away%20in%201993.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPallab%20has%20my%20unwavering%20attention%20as%20he%20narrates%20his%20story%2C%20a%20tale%20that%20takes%20me%20back%20to%20an%20Enid%20Blyton%20adventure.%20He%2C%20along%20with%20his%20parents%20Prosanta%20Kumar%20and%20Supriya%20Roy%2C%20his%20wife%20Sudeshna%2C%20his%20son%20Saurav%2C%20and%20his%20daughter-in-law%20Priya%2C%20would%20in%20the%20coming%20days%20take%20upon%20them%20the%20arduous%20task%20of%20restoring%20the%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20of%20the%20Roys%20(Rajbari)%20to%20its%20former%20glory.%20The%20goal%20was%20to%20turn%20this%20spectral%20ruin%20into%20a%20liveable%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Operation%20clean-up%E2%80%99%3A%20Battling%20snakes%20and%20lizards%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20began%20approaching%20one%20room%20at%20a%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pallab%20says%20as%20he%20recalls%20the%20renovation%20process.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20only%20when%20%E2%80%98operation%20clean-up%E2%80%99%20commenced%20that%20the%20family%20could%20ascertain%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20devastation.%20The%20years%20of%20isolation%20had%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20the%20royal%20beauty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInsects%2C%20five-inch%20thick%20layers%20of%20dust%20and%20crumbling%20roofs%20marred%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20restore%20what%20had%20once%20been%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F341653%2Funique-homestay-in-goa-maharashtra-sawantwadi-palace-hotel-run-by-royal-family-sawant-bhonsle%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymbol%20of%20grandeur%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20place%20was%20infested%20with%20snakes%20and%20monitor%20lizards%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pallab%20exclaims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1726572982.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20of%20the%20Roys%20(Rajbari)%20is%20an%2018th%20century%20marvel%20in%20Murshidabad%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1726572982.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1726572982-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1726572982-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1726572982-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1726572982-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-366171%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20of%20the%20Roys%20(Rajbari)%20is%20an%2018th-century%20marvel%20in%20Murshidabad.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1-1726573107.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20300-year-old%20palace%20was%20in%20a%20state%20of%20disrepair%20after%20the%20death%20of%20Raja%20Kamalaranjan%20Roy%20in%201993%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1-1726573107.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1-1726573107-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1-1726573107-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1-1726573107-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-1-1726573107-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-366173%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20300-year-old%20palace%20was%20in%20a%20state%20of%20disrepair%20after%20the%20death%20of%20Raja%20Kamalaranjan%20Roy%20in%201993.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20family%20scoured%20the%20rooms%20of%20the%20ancestral%20palace%2C%20attempting%20to%20identify%20the%20degree%20of%20cleaning%20each%20required%2C%20they%20were%20met%20with%20more%20surprises%2C%20or%20rather%20shocks.%20%E2%80%9CSome%20rooms%E2%80%99%20arches%20were%20blocked%20with%20bricks.%20When%20we%20managed%20to%20get%20into%20the%20rooms%2C%20we%20noticed%20that%20the%20doors%20and%20windows%20had%20vanished.%20We%20guessed%20that%20they%20had%20been%20vandalised%20or%20eaten%20by%20termites.%20Even%20some%20of%20the%20supporting%20beams%20were%20missing%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pallab%20recalls.%20The%20cleaning%20spree%20went%20on%20for%20years%2C%20yielding%20three%20rooms%20that%20were%20deemed%20fit%20to%20live%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20family%20decided%20to%20turn%20the%20ancestral%20palace%20into%20a%20guesthouse.%20However%2C%20Pallab%20explains%20that%20the%20plan%20flopped%20as%20social%20media%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20as%20popular%20back%20then%20and%20most%20people%E2%80%99s%20first%20choice%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20guest%20house.%20It%20seemed%20like%20the%2018th-century%20palace%20would%20remain%20desolate.%20Unable%20to%20watch%20their%20ancestral%20pride%20meet%20such%20a%20fate%2C%20the%20Roy%20family%20decided%20to%20rebuild%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F332940%2Fdevpur-royal-homestay-darbargadh-in-kutch-jadeja-family-runs-farmstay-cbse-school%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroyal%20residence%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20soon%20become%20a%20heritage%20hotel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Buckingham%20of%20India%E2%80%99%3A%20Reviving%20a%20lost%20legacy%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20heyday%2C%20the%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20would%20have%20earned%20the%20%E2%80%98Buckingham%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20moniker.%20Explaining%20the%20comparison%2C%20Pallab%20shares%20that%20the%20palace%E2%80%99s%20functioning%20was%20in%20tune%20with%20colonial%20times%20and%20its%20practices%20mirrored%20those%20at%20Buckingham%20Palace%20in%20England.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20British%20Government%20had%20a%20system%20of%20administering%20estates%20through%20the%20Court%20of%20Wards%20if%20the%20person%20in%20power%20was%20a%20minor%20and%20the%20guardian%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20present.%20Across%20the%2010%20generations%20of%20our%20family%2C%20three%20generations%20have%20seen%20their%20owners%20die%20young.%20And%20so%2C%20for%20almost%2045%20years%2C%20the%20British%20Government%20administered%20the%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pallab%20recalls.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20grandfather%20%E2%80%93%20who%20lost%20his%20father%20at%20the%20age%20of%20six%20months%20%E2%80%93%20was%20brought%20up%20by%20a%20British%20governess%20for%20six%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-2-1726573228.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20of%20the%20Roys%20(Rajbari)%20has%20been%20restored%20to%20its%20former%20glory%20and%20is%20now%20a%20plush%20heritage%20hotel%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-2-1726573228.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-2-1726573228-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-2-1726573228-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-2-1726573228-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-2-1726573228-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-366175%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20of%20the%20Roys%20(Rajbari)%20has%20been%20restored%20to%20its%20former%20glory%20and%20is%20now%20a%20plush%20heritage%20hotel.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-3-1726573323.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20of%20the%20Roys%20(Rajbari)%20boasts%2014%20rooms%20which%20can%20accommodate%20a%20total%20of%2040%20guests%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-3-1726573323.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-3-1726573323-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-3-1726573323-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-3-1726573323-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fcossimbazar-palace-in-india-3-1726573323-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-366177%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20of%20the%20Roys%20(Rajbari)%20boasts%2014%20rooms%20which%20can%20accommodate%20a%20total%20of%2040%20guests.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20delve%20further%20into%20history%2C%20Pallab%20draws%20attention%20to%20the%20notable%20parallels%20between%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%E2%80%99s%20functions%20and%20those%20of%20the%20palaces%20in%20England.%20%E2%80%9CAround%201924%2C%20the%20house%20had%20200%20guards.%20There%20was%20also%20the%20%E2%80%98Changing%20of%20the%20Guard%E2%80%99%20ceremony%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F48468%2Flieutenant-colonel-sophia-qureshi-indian-army%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emilitary%20drills%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20were%2034%20gardeners%2C%20innumerable%20staff%20and%20nine%20functioning%20kitchens.%E2%80%9D%20He%20laughs%20as%20he%20recounts%20the%20famous%20tea%20parties%20held%20at%20Cossimbazar%20Palace.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20crockery%20and%20cutlery%20for%20these%20were%20imported%20from%20England!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20in%201947%2C%20as%20India%20got%20freedom%2C%20and%20the%20estate%20system%20was%20abolished%20soon%20after%2C%20the%20fate%20of%20Cossimbazar%20Palace%20took%20a%20drastic%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FVZaaCzClgxA%3Fsi%3D1WO9zmnnvPyi5MQ3%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20assets%20in%20our%20family%20were%20self-earned%20over%2010%20generations%3B%20they%20were%20not%20grants%20from%20the%20Government.%20But%20everything%20went%20away%20without%20a%20single%20%3Cem%3Epaisa%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Indian%20currency%20denomination)%3B%20they%20were%20auctioned.%20I%20have%20heard%20stories%20of%20how%20everything%20vanished%20overnight%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pallab%20laments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20grandfather%20would%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98From%20a%20king%2C%20I%20became%20a%20pauper%E2%80%99.%20The%20staff%20at%20the%20estate%2C%20the%20Government%2C%20and%20the%20system%20turned%20against%20him%20as%20dues%2C%20penalties%2C%20arrears%2C%20and%20international%20income%20issues%20began%20to%20surface.%20It%20was%20a%20miserable%20situation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20solution%20that%20Raja%20Kamalaranjan%20Roy%20saw%20was%20to%20leave%20behind%20his%20Murshidabad%20house%20and%20shift%20to%20Kolkata%20with%20his%20family.%20It%20was%20here%20that%20Pallab%E2%80%99s%20parents%20married%20and%20a%20major%20part%20of%20his%20life%20would%20be%20spent%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F333208%2Fwhere-to-eat-in-kolkata-classics-best-heritage-eateries-map-anindya-basu-dolon-dutta%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98City%20of%20Joy%E2%80%99%3C%2F